DromeAudio
------------------------------------------
DromeAudio is a small audio manipulation and playback library that's written in
C++. It features a simple API for loading, generating, processing, and playing
audio.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.2-1
  libDromeAudio-devel-0.3.0-1bl2
  libDromeAudio0-0.3.0-1bl2
  libgcc1-11.2.0-1
  libstdc++6-11.2.0-1
  libvorbisfile3-1.3.6-1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.37-2
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.2.0-1
  gcc-objc-11.2.0-1
  gcc-objc++-11.2.0-1
  libvorbis-devel-1.3.6-1
  ninja-1.10.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/joshb/DromeAudio

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/joshb/DromeAudio/archive/refs/tags/v0.3.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack DromeAudio-0.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./DromeAudio-0.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/DromeAudio-0.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/DromeAudio-0.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libDromeAudio0-0.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libDromeAudio-devel-0.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(DromeAudio)
